# Files that must never be uploaded to a Vercel build.
#
# A CLI deploy (`vercel deploy`) uploads the working directory. A local .env
# would then be sourced by the build (scripts/db-deploy.sh) and its development
# DATABASE_URL (localhost) would override the DATABASE_URL Vercel injects for
# that environment — build-time migrations then fail with ECONNREFUSED against
# 127.0.0.1:5432. Vercel injects every env var directly, so no .env file should
# ever reach a build. See docs/setup/deployment.md.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Local-only artifacts (also covered by .gitignore, but a CLI upload doesn't
# read .gitignore).
.git
node_modules
.next
test-results
playwright-report
blob-report
